cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with deep learning for semantic matching, which is a task related to computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new deep network architecture, which involves training with weak image-level labels, indicating that it may fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on cross-instance and cross-category matching tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
